---
import ServicePage from '../../components/ServicePage.astro';
---
<ServicePage
	title="in Clapham"
	highlight="Men\'s Health"
	heroSubtitle="Expert pelvic health physiotherapy for men — addressing pelvic floor, bladder, bowel, and sexual function concerns with discretion and clinical rigour."
	breadcrumb="Men\'s Health"
	seoTitle="Men\'s Health in Clapham"
	seoDescription="Men\'s health physiotherapy in Clapham. Pelvic floor rehab, post-prostate recovery, pelvic pain, and bladder or bowel symptoms treated with discretion."
	intro={[
		"Men\'s health physiotherapy focuses on conditions affecting the pelvic floor, bladder, bowel, and sexual function.",
		"At Balance, we take a structured and clinical approach to assessment and treatment. We identify the underlying drivers of your symptoms and build a clear plan to restore function, reduce pain, and improve confidence.",
		"These issues are often under-reported, but they are both common and highly treatable with the right approach.",
	]}
	whenHeading="When to consider"
	whenHighlight="an assessment"
	whenList={[
		"Persistent pelvic pain (perineum, testicles, lower abdomen)",
		"Urinary symptoms such as leaking, urgency, or difficulty starting flow",
		"Post-prostate surgery symptoms (e.g. dribbling or incontinence)",
		"Bowel dysfunction, including poor control or chronic constipation",
		"Pain related to cycling or prolonged sitting",
		"Sexual dysfunction linked to pelvic floor function",
	]}
	howHeading="How we"
	howHighlight="treat"
	howList={[
		"Pelvic floor assessment (external and, where appropriate, internal)",
		"Targeted strengthening or down-training of the pelvic floor",
		"Hands-on therapy to reduce tension and improve tissue function",
		"Breathing and relaxation strategies to reduce overactivity",
		"Postural and load management advice",
		"Gradual return to exercise and activity",
	]}
	whoHeading="Who we"
	whoHighlight="help"
	whoList={[
		"Post-surgical patients recovering from prostate or bladder procedures",
		"Cyclists and active individuals managing pelvic pain",
		"Sedentary workers addressing pelvic tension from prolonged sitting",
		"Chronic pelvic pain patients where symptoms have persisted",
	]}
	faqs={[
		{ q: "Is this only for prostate-related issues?", a: "No. We treat a wide range of pelvic health conditions, including pain, bladder, and bowel symptoms." },
		{ q: "What happens in the first session?", a: "A detailed discussion followed by assessment of movement, breathing, and pelvic floor function where appropriate." },
		{ q: "Is internal assessment required?", a: "No. It is optional and only performed with your consent." },
		{ q: "Can physiotherapy help with cycling-related pain?", a: "Yes. We address both mechanical load and pelvic floor tension to reduce symptoms." },
		{ q: "How many sessions will I need?", a: "This varies, but most people improve over a short course of structured rehabilitation." },
		{ q: "Do I need a referral?", a: "No. You can book directly, though some insurers may require one." },
		{ q: "Is it confidential?", a: "Yes. All consultations are private and handled with discretion." },
	]}
/>
